      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "vide",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " 'Robinson,' vol. 3. App. 166; and cf. Tristram, 'The Land of Israel, p. 483); but the narrative appears to say that Mahanaim lay not north of Ga-leed, but between that place and Jabbok. Hence Porter suggests Gerasa, the most splendid ruin east of the Jordan, and bordering on the Jabbok, as occupying the site of Mahanaim (",
        "children": []
